  "title": "Lumbar puncture",
  "body_html": "<b>Lumbar Puncture Key Points</b><br /><br /><ul><li>An LP should be performed at the L3/L4 or L4/L5 space as the spinal cord terminates at L1-L2</li><li>The first 'give' of the needle is when the ligamentum flavum is pierced and the second 'give' is when the dura is pierced</li><li>Normal opening pressure is between 10-25 cm H<sub>2</sub>O in an adult</li><li>Post procedure headache is common (up to 38%)</li></ul><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti898b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti898.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></CENTER><div class='imagetext'><b>Click on image to enlarge</b></div><br /><br /><b>Layers pierced during lumbar puncture:</b><br /><ul><li>Skin</li><li>Subcutaneous tissue (fat and fascia)</li><li>Supraspinous ligament</li><li>Interspinous ligament</li><li>Ligamentum flavum</li><li>Extradural space</li><li>Dura mater</li><li>Subdural space</li><li>Arachnoid mater</li><li>Subarachnoid space</li></ul></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodylinks\"><table style='width:100%'><tr><td>BMJ</td><td style = \"float: right;width:115px;\"><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_like_563\" data-linkid=\"563\" data-rating=\"1\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-up\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_good_count_563\" class = \"link_good_count\" style=\"color:green; font-size:85%;\">0</span><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_dislike_563\" data-linkid=\"563\" data-rating=\"0\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-down\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-down\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_bad_count_563\" class = \"link_bad_count\" style=\"color:red; font-size:85%;\">0</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://pn.bmj.com/content/14/6/380\">A practical approach to, diagnosis, assessment and management of idiopathic intracranial hypertension</a></td></tr></table><br><br><table style='width:100%'><tr><td>Pubmed</td><td style = \"float: right;width:115px;\"><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_like_562\" data-linkid=\"562\" data-rating=\"1\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-up\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_good_count_562\" class = \"link_good_count\" style=\"color:green; font-size:85%;\">0</span><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_dislike_562\" data-linkid=\"562\" data-rating=\"0\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-down\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-down\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_bad_count_562\" class = \"link_bad_count\" style=\"color:red; font-size:85%;\">0</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25133881/\">Cerebrospinal fluid pressure in adults</a></td></tr></table></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodymedia\"></div>\n\n\n<div id=\"categorynum\">1</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategorynum\">1</div>\n\n<div id=\"categoryname\">Anatomy</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategoryname\">Abdomen & pelvis</div>\n<div id=\"mybody\">\n\n<div id=\"body_content\">\n<b>Lumbar Puncture Key Points</b><br /><br /><ul><li>An LP should be performed at the L3/L4 or L4/L5 space as the spinal cord terminates at L1-L2</li><li>The first 'give' of the needle is when the ligamentum flavum is pierced and the second 'give' is when the dura is pierced</li><li>Normal opening pressure is between 10-25 cm H<sub>2</sub>O in an adult</li><li>Post procedure headache is common (up to 38%)</li></ul><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='gro